To replace the `HiArrowRight` icon with the `<span>` element containing "DESIGNS" on hover, you can manage this by toggling the display property of these elements based on a hover state. Since you are using React, your goal can be reached using some extra CSS for showing and hiding elements on the hover state of the parent `<div>`.

Below is an example of how you might update your `ProjectsBtn` component to achieve the desired functionality:

Firstly, add the classes needed to control the visibility on hover inside your component:

```jsx
import Image from "next/image";
import Link from "next/link";

import { HiArrowRight } from "react-icons/hi2";

const ProjectsBtn = () => {
  return (
    <div className="mx-auto xl:mx-0 group">
      <Link
        href="/designs"
        className="relative w-[185px] h-[185px] flex justify-center items-center bg-circleStar bg-cover bg-center bg-no-repeat"
